defaultSome of t
defaulthose within this group 
defaultwho have lesser disabilities will
default find that they are unable to claim Employment and Support Allowance or Perso
defaultnal Independence Payments
default and that they must now pay some Council Tax
default for the first time
default.  If they
default live in social housing and their children have moved away
default, which is ofte
defaultn the case, the ‘bedroom tax’ 
defaultwill also come into play.
default&#xa0;
defaultThis group – older out-of-work couples – is especially numerous in many older industrial areas, where meaningful job opportuni
defaultties 
defaultfor them 
defaulthave long since dried up.  They will often find that the cumulative effect of the reforms is to push them down to the poverty line.
